KATSINA – The President, Nigeria Union of Local Government Employees, (NULGE) Katsina state chapter, Comrade Nasiru Wada Mai’adua has called for the establishment of statistics unit in all the 34 local council areas of the state. The President stated this in an interview with some journalists in his office on Thursday. According to him, the establishment of the unit at the local government level would assist in keeping an up-to-date record of service of all workers. PENGASSAN Will Only Support Deregulation Exercise Based On… 161 Personnel Of Private Security Company Protest 35 Months… He noted that records such as the economic potentials of the area can easily be accessed through the unit. “Planning on education, health and distribution of social amenities can be made easier through data generated by the unit. “We have encouraged the state local government service commission to consider establishing the unit for easier accessibility of staff record. Similarly, Wada called for the progression of promotion of local government staff to level GL 16, arguing that, their stagnation on level GL 15 is not doing good to the service and the state in general. The President however disclosed that the state Governor, Alhaji Aminu Bello Masari had set-up a committee to address the issue.